Package leeLogger

Interface Loggable

All Known Implementing Classes:
Logger
public interface Loggable
Interface specifies the methods that a Loggable program should have. The Logger interface specifies in broad outline what the functions are that a class that inherits from the Loggable interface should be able to perform. These include being able to log data to a database, and read data from a user. The data is specified as type Transactions in this case or any of the subclasses of a Transactions parent class.

leefowler
